(107, 'photo/52e3395f12ee1.jpg', 'Kuching - Kuching Fullboard', 0, '4D3N Kuching Fullboard (Min 2 pax)', '<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><br /></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"contentArial-black\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> </span></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>DAY 01 ARRIVAL / CITY TOUR / CHECK IN (D)</strong><br />Arrivals  at the Kuching International Airport, meet and greet; and then proceed  with Kuching City Tour.&nbsp; Experience the glorious heritage of people  whose origins are shrouded in the mists of time.&nbsp; Tours include a visit  to Sarawak museum, Kuching waterfront, the state parliament house, state  mosque, main bazaar, civic centre and else.&nbsp;&nbsp; Dinner at local  restaurant before check in<br /><strong><br />DAY 02&nbsp; SEMENGGOH ORG UTAN/ JONG CROCODILE FARM/ ANNAH RAIS (B/L/D)</strong><br />Breakfast  at hotel, then transfer to Semenggoh Orang Utan where you can view the  Orang Utan who have been rescued from captivity and trained to survive  in the natural surrounding.&nbsp; They roam freely in the rainforest and  often return to the centre at feeding time (9am @ 3pm).&nbsp; Then precede  tour to Jong&rsquo;s Crocodile Farm which is nestled among tropical fruit  trees &amp; greenery &amp; is the haunt of over 1000 crocodiles.&nbsp; You  can also find other animals such as monkeys, barking deer etc in this  farm.&nbsp; Lunch will be taken place at local restaurant before proceed tour  to Annah Rais Longhouse.&nbsp; This preserves bamboo longhouse previously  known as Land Dayak during the British Colonial rule.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll learn the  unique architectural &amp; cultural features of the longhouse and the  traditional farming style of Bidayuh peoples.&nbsp; Dinner will be taken  place at local restaurant then back to hotel&nbsp; <br /><strong><br />DAY 03 SARAWAK CULTURAL VILLAGE / FAIRY &amp; WIND CAVE (B/L/D)</strong><br />Breakfast  at hotel, and then proceed for Sarawak Cultural Village which located  at the foot of Mount Santubong.&nbsp;&nbsp; This living museum showcasing 7 major  communities in Sarawak &ndash; Iban, Bidayuh, Melanau, Orang Ulu, Penan,  Chinese &amp; Malay.&nbsp; Here, you can learn &amp; explore their tradition  and activities.&nbsp; Get the chance to watch their traditional dance  performance at the theatre.&nbsp; Lunch at local restaurant before you  proceed to Fairy &amp; Wind Cave; there are stalactite &amp; stalagmite  formations on the floor of the caves that resemble figures &amp;  animals.&nbsp; Wind cave ends overlooking a schedule river scene that will  definitely take your breath away.&nbsp; Dinner will be taken place at local  restaurant before back to hotel&nbsp; <br /><strong>&nbsp;<br />DAY 04 KUCHING CITY TOUR / DEPARTURE (B)</strong><br />Breakfast at hotel, free at own leisure before time for departure</span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Includes </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">- Return airport hotel transfer<br />- 03 night&rsquo;s accommodation at selected hotel<br />- Daily Breakfast , 02 Lunches &amp; 03 Dinners<br />- All tours &amp; transfer stated in itinerary<br />- Entrance Fees</span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><br /></span></span> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Excludes</strong><br /></span></span> <span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"contentArial-black\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\"> </span></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">- Airfare and all type of taxes<br />- Travel, PA or Repatriation insurance<br />- Tipping and potterages fees<br />- High Season charge at certain hotels (TBA &ndash; Please refer Malaysia&rsquo;s Calendar)<br /><br /></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> </span></span></p><table style=\"width: 438px; height: 104px;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" background=\"images/frame_a.jpg\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><br /></span></span></td></tr><tr><td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" background=\"images/frame_b.jpg\"><table style=\"width: 421px; height: 87px;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0