(116, 'photo/5514b9326d38b.jpg', 'Korea', 1, '8D6N Seoul + Jeju Island ', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">8 DAYS 6 NIGHTS KOREA ~ SEOUL + JEJU ISLAND + GANGWONDO</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KUCHING / KUALA LUMPUR</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">AK5227 KCH/KUL 1945-2125</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Departure to Kuala Lumpur, connecting the flight to Incheon.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 2&nbsp;&nbsp; KUALA LUMPUR / INCHEON / JEJU&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Lunch / Dinner)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">D7506 KUL/ICN 0100-0820</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Upon arrival at<strong> Incheon International Airport, m</strong>eet and greet by professional tour guide.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span class=\"st\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Bukchon </span></strong></span><em><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Hanok Village</span></strong></em><span class=\"st\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"> is a Korean traditional village with a long history.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Gwanghwamun</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> Seoul Landmark.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span class=\"onshow\"><strong><span>Cheong Wa Dae</span></strong></span><span class=\"onshow\"><span> is the imposing official residence of South Korea&rsquo;s president.</span></span><span> </span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><em><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></em><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Shopping at <strong>Dongdaemun Market</strong>, the largest and oldest shopping place in Seoul. </span><em></em></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Transfer to domestic airport for your flight to Jeju Island.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span>Yongduam Rock </span></strong><span>an unusual lava</span><span> f</span><span>ormation that look like a roaring dragon rising from the sea into the sky. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 3&nbsp;&nbsp; Jeju&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span>Visit the <strong>Seongsan Sunrise Peak</strong></span><span>, where you can enjoy the spectacular natural surroundings.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span>Explore <strong>Seonyep Folk Village</strong>, a folk and history museum with miniature display of traditional villages.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Proceed to <strong>Seojikoji</strong>, the filming site of the famous Korean series drama &ldquo;All In&rdquo; which located at east coast of the Jeju Island.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Drop by<strong> Yakcheonsa</strong>, which means &lsquo;temple where medicinal water flows. Around the temples you can also find many short Jeju Oranges trees.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span>End the day with some Korea&rsquo;s traditional tea culture appreciation at the <strong>O&rsquo;sulloc Tea museum.</strong></span><strong></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span>Visit <strong>Mysterious Road</strong>, experience the strange phenomenon of going uphill when your vehicle&rsquo;s engine is turned off.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 4&nbsp;&nbsp; Jeju - Gimpo - Gangwondo&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; T</span><span>ake domestic flights from Jeju to Gimpo Domestic airport.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span>Experience Kimchi making,</span></strong><span> fresh Ginseng juice<strong> </strong>and <strong>trying out Korea traditional Costumes</strong> for picture taking.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><span>Take a ferry to <strong>Nami Island</strong> the symbolic backdrop of mega hit Korean drama &ldquo;Winter Sonata&rdquo;. You can feel the excitement of the romantic drama and take a walk down beautiful tree-lined paths with your loved ones featured in the most memorable scenes. </span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span>-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span>Great experience to enjoy <strong>hot spring</strong> facility in the resort rich with mineral. It not only can healing the body and mind.*( Pse bring along swimming suits and cap )<strong></strong></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 5&nbsp;&nbsp; Gangwondo-Yongin&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Seoraksan</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> is the third highest mountain in South Korea. <strong>Bronze Buddha of Sinheungsa</strong>. (Buddhist Temple) in Seoraksan National Park.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Drop by <strong>Teddy Bear Farm </strong>where is display at the garden and gallery.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Proceed to <strong>Daepohang Fish Market</strong> where you can taste the fresh sashimi own expense</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 6&nbsp;&nbsp; Gangwondo &ndash; Seoul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n