(113, 'photo/59229687a28c5.jpg', 'PSTT04 Sarawak Cultural Village', 1, 'ç ‚æ‹‰è¶Šæ–‡åŒ–æ‘Half Day - Min. 2 Person', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Sarawak Cultural Village. Popularly known as the &ldquo;Living Museum&rsquo;, the Village is a showcase of kaleidoscope of Sarawak&rsquo;s cultures and traditions. On arrival, you will explore the 7 authentic replicas of ethnic houses; Chinese Farm House, Malay Stilted House, Melanau Tall House, Penan Hut as well Longhouse of the Iban, Bidayuh and Orang Ulu. Displayed in each houses are the many artifacts made by the individual dwellers. </span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">Demonstration of arts and crafts like beadwork, wood and bamboo carvings, &lsquo;Pua&rsquo; and straw weaving can be seenwhile touring the Village. You also will be entertained with 45 minutes of the traditional dances of the various ethnic tribes of Sarawak at the Village theatre. Shows are fixed daily at 1130hrs &ndash; 1215hrs and 1600hrs &ndash; 1645hrs<strong>.</strong></span></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\">&ldquo;<span lang=\"ZH-CN\">åŠå¤©çœ‹éç ‚æ‹‰è¶Š</span>&rdquo;<span lang=\"ZH-CN\">å¯ä»¥åœ¨ç ‚æ‹‰è¶Šæ–‡åŒ–æ‘å®Œæˆã€‚é‡Œå¤´å¤åˆ¶äº†æœ‰ä¸åŒçš„å»ºç­‘ç‰©ï¼Œä»£è¡¨ç€ç ‚æ‹‰è¶Šæ¯ä¸€ä¸ªä¸»è¦çš„æ—ç¾¤ã€‚æ‰€æœ‰çš„æ¨¡åž‹å»ºç­‘ç‰©æ”¾ç½®äº†å„ç§æ—ç¾¤ï¼Œè¿˜ç©¿ä¸Šä¼ ç»Ÿæœé¥°ï¼Œè¿›è¡Œç€æ—¥æ—¥å¸¸çš„ç”Ÿæ´»ã€‚å‚è§‚å®Œæ¯•åŽï¼Œæ‚¨å¯ä»¥åœ¨æ–‡åŒ–æ‘é‡Œçš„å‰§åœºè§‚èµå¤šå…ƒæ–‡åŒ–çš„èˆžè¹ˆè¡¨æ¼”ã€‚æ‚¨äº¦å¯ä»¥åˆ°é‚£é‡Œçš„é¤é¦†ç”¨é¤åŠåœ¨æ‰‹å·¥è‰ºå“å•†åº—è´­ç‰©ã€‚</span></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, p