(112, 'photo/5302d713014bb.jpg', 'Kuching - Land Dayak / Bidayuh Longhouse', 0, 'Land Dayak / Bidayuh Longhouse (Half Day) (Min 2 Person)', '<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"heading4\">Land Dayak / Bidayuh Longhouse</span><span class=\"contentArial-red\"><br />Half Day&nbsp;Min 2 Person&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><br /><span class=\"contentArial-red\">Description</span><br /></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Located about 70km from Kuching, This bidayuh longhouse Anah Rais, still preserved its traditional look. They stayed in a house made from well preserved bamboo which is called Longhouse. Here guest can view and walk on the unique architectural and cultural features of longhouse and traditional farming lifestyle of the Bidayuh peoples. They built imposing octagonal skull houses ( BARUK )&nbsp; to house they enemy&rsquo;s head. The original longhouse is over a century old and many biliks are now vacant as the younger generation move to the towns and cities in search of work and education. Visit with some of the older folks and learn their traditions.</span></span></span></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong><span class=\"contentArial-red\">Includes</span></strong><br /></span></span></span></span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">- Tours as per itinerary&nbsp;<br />- Transportation&nbsp;<br />- Entrance Fees&nbsp;<br />- English, Malay or Mandarin Speaking Guide</span></span></span></span></span></p>'),
