 class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">大阪市内酒店</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong>Hotel in Osaka</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">奈良</span> Nara</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">日本历史最悠久的古都</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">天然野生鹿公园</span> Deer Park</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">日本最大的天然野生鹿公园</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">东大寺</span>-<span lang=\"ZH-CN\">大佛殿</span> Todaiji</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">曾经一度是世界最大木造建筑物，里面坐有日本最古老的佛像</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">神户港口</span> Kobe Port</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">世界有名的神户，尤其是其港口的夜景更是全日本有名</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">神户唐人街</span> China Town</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">历史悠久的日本唐人街，中国国父孙中山亦在此活跃过</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td rowspan=\"4\" width=\"83\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong>Day 8</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">梅田</span> Umeda</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">大阪最高级市中心</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td rowspan=\"4\" width=\"49\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">B/L/D</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td rowspan=\"4\" width=\"118\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">心斋桥</span> Shinsaibashi</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">日本最长商店街，最大地下街亦在此</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">难波</span> Namba</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">大阪最热闹</span>DOWNTOWN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">関西</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">✈吉隆坡</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>D7535 KIX/KUL 2335-0520</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"83\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong>Day 9</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"189\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">吉隆坡✈古晋</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"310\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>AK5232 KUL/KCH 0830-1015</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"49\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"118\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\" width=\"749\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong>** <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">行程安排順序或不可抗拒因素以當地地接旅行社為主</span> **</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'Yes', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00', '0000-00-00', 0, '1', NULL, '2021-11-08 16:52:47'),
(108, 4, 'photo/6188b226d18a4.jpg', 'PSTT09 Bako National Park', '', '', '', 'å³‡å“¥å›½å®¶å…¬å›­Full Day - Min. 2 pax', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Bako National Park, the first gazette national park in Sarawak. Bako was established as a national park in 1957. Since then, it has offered its visitors the perfect introduction to Sarawak&rsquo;s native vegetation and wildlife.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">There are 16 trails that explore the diversity of the park. The most popular takes you in search of the shy pot-bellied Proboscis Monkeys. Catch them as they come to riverbanks to feed before they head for the cool depths of the forests when the day heats up. Another popular trail explores the mangrove swamps where most of its denizens are equipped to live both on land and underwater.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">You also will see winding creepers and vines, long tailed macaques and silver leaf monkeys, wild boars, squirrels, monitor lizards and many other animals.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">*<em>Please note that these animals are wild and therefore, there is no guarantee that visitors will see them.</em></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpFirst\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">峇哥国家公园被喻为最典型的砂拉越森林与生态保护区。这里有沼泽森林、磨砂状的平原植被、红树林、龙脑香林、细腻的悬崖植被等，基本上婆罗洲岛上的植被大多可以在峇哥找到。此外，峇哥还有丰富的野生生态物种，而其海岸线包含小海湾、山凹和沙滩。公园内的步道有清楚的标示，便于游客徒步或远征。在这里，长尾猴和银叶猴很常见，山猪也经常出现在公园总部，另有松鼠和巨蜥也是这里的常客。下午时分，您还有机会看到罕见的长鼻猴。峇哥国家公园内的植物种类丰富，而且易于观察。所有步道都穿梭在不同的植被中，从长达</span>80<span lang=\"ZH-CN\">米硕大的龙脑香，到密集的红树林都可以在此找到。峇哥也有许多不错的白沙滩，可以作为森林徒步的歇息地点，其中&ldquo;小直落班丹&rdquo;是极为美丽幽静的海湾。所有海滩皆可以看见石灰岩与砂岩构成的峭壁，海浪海风长年累月在石上留下各种痕迹，形成当地著名的&ldquo;海栈&rdquo;。傍晚时分，您还可以看见成千上百的雨燕，在沙滩尽头岩壁上的巢穴附近盘旋飞舞。</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Tour Duration: Full day</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 135px;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'Yes', '', 0, 'bako, sarawak, borneo', 'Bako National Park, the first gazette national park in Sarawak. Bako was established as a national park in 1957.', '0000-00-00', '0000-00-00', 0, '1', NULL, '2021-11-17 10:52:28'),
(116, 5, 'photo/5514b9326d38b.jpg', 'Korea', '', '', '', '8D6N Seoul + Jeju Island ', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">8 DAYS 6 NIGHTS KOREA ~ SEOUL + JEJU ISLAND + GANGWONDO</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KUCHING / KUALA LUMPUR</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">AK5227 KCH/KUL 1945-2125</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Departure to Kuala Lumpur, connecting the flight to Incheon.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 2&nbsp;&nbsp; KUALA LUMPUR / INCHEON / JEJU&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Lunch / Dinner)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">D7506 KUL/ICN 0100-0820</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Upon arrival at<strong> Incheon International Airport, m</strong>eet and greet by professional tour guide.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span class=\"st\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Bukchon </span></strong></span><em><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Hanok Village</span></strong></em><span class=\"st\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"> is a Korean traditional village with a long history.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Gwanghwamun</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> Seoul Landmark.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span class=\"onshow\"><strong>Cheong Wa Dae</strong></span><span class=\"onshow\"> is the imposing official residence of South Korea&rsquo;s president.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><em><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></em><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Shopping at <strong>Dongdaemun Market</strong>, the largest and oldest shopping place in Seoul. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Transfer to domestic airport for your flight to Jeju Island.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong>Yongduam Rock </strong>an unusual lava formation that look like a roaring dragon rising from the sea into the sky.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 3&nbsp;&nbsp; Jeju&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]-->Visit the <strong>Seongsan Sunrise Peak</strong>, where you can enjoy the spectacular natural surroundings.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]-->Explore <strong>Seonyep Folk Village</strong>, a folk and history museum with miniature display of traditional villages.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Proceed to <strong>Seojikoji</strong>, the filming site of the famous Korean series drama &ldquo;All In&rdquo; which located at east coast of the Jeju Island.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Drop by<strong> Yakcheonsa</strong>, which means &lsquo;temple where medicinal water flows. Around the temples you can also find many short Jeju Oranges trees.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]-->End the day with some Korea&rsquo;s traditional tea culture appreciation at the <strong>O&rsquo;sulloc Tea museum.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]-->Visit <strong>Mysterious Road</strong>, experience the strange phenomenon of going uphill when your vehicle&rsquo;s engine is turned off.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 4&nbsp;&nbsp; Jeju - Gimpo - Gangwondo&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; T</span>ake domestic flights from Jeju to Gimpo Domestic airport.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong>Experience Kimchi making,</strong> fresh Ginseng juice and <strong>trying out Korea traditional Costumes</strong> for picture taking.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong>Take a ferry to <strong>Nami Island</strong> the symbolic backdrop of mega hit Korean drama &ldquo;Winter Sonata&rdquo;. You can feel the excitement of the romantic drama and take a walk down beautiful tree-lined paths with your loved ones featured in the most memorable scenes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]-->-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <!--[endif]-->Great experience to enjoy <strong>hot spring</strong> facility in the resort rich with mineral. It not only can healing the body and mind.*( Pse bring along swimming suits and cap )</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 5&nbsp;&nbsp; Gangwondo-Yongin&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Seoraksan</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> is the third highest mountain in South Korea. <strong>Bronze Buddha of Sinheungsa</strong>. (Buddhist Temple) in Seoraksan National Park.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Drop by <strong>Teddy Bear Farm </strong>where is display at the garden and gallery.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Proceed to <strong>Daepohang Fish Market</strong> where you can taste the fresh sashimi own expense</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 6&nbsp;&nbsp; Gangwondo &ndash; Seoul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast/Dinner)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]-->-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <!--[endif]-->Proceed to <strong>Everland ( Free Pass Ticket )</strong>, a full-filled theme park to enjoy thrilling rides and a galore of lively entertainment<em>. ** Lunch own arrangement.*(If weather no permitted replaced by Lotte world theme park )</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Enjoy </span><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Outdoor ski experience</span></strong> <span lang=\"EN-US\">(optional ski equipment &amp; ski suits US$60.00p/p,&nbsp;&nbsp; include free training )</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Seoul&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">(Breakfast /Lunch /Dinner)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Shop by the <strong>Ginseng Outlet, Liverin outlet,&nbsp; Duty Free cosmetic shop &amp; Amethyst Factory</strong></span><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Snap photo at<strong> Love Lock desk at N-Tower</strong></span><strong>, </strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">shooting place for 2014 hits Korea drama <em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;My Love From The Star&rdquo; </span></em>. <em>*( Excluded N-Tower Observatory desk )</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">Shopping at <strong>Myeondong Fashion Street</strong>, a major shopping district lined with shops selling quality-branded goods .</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Day 8&nbsp;&nbsp; INCHEON / KUALA LUMPUR / KUCHING&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (Breakfast<em>)</em>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">D7507 ICN/KUL 1115-1700</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">AK5228 KUL/KCH 1920-2105</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><!-- [if !supportLists]-->-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <!--[endif]--><strong>Local Food Product Shop</strong> for purchasing some authentic Korean local products.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-US\">-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">Transfer to the airport</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-US\"> for your flight back home</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-US\">SQUENCE OF ITINERARY SUBJECT TO LOCAL ARRANGEMENT</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Special Meals included</strong>:</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Breakfast will serve American Breakfast or Chinese cum Local Korean Style. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Lunch &amp; Dinner: Jeju Black Pork Bulgogi, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Seafood Steamboat, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Chinese Style Meal 5dishes + 1soup, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Korean style Pork BBQ X 2 Times, Ginseng Chicken</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"> Soup + Ginseng Wine + Noodle</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">, Bimbibap + steamboat</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">, </span><span lang=\"EN-US\">Dalgabi, Mushroom Steamboat</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Accommodations:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(2N) Jeju Palace Hotel / Jeju Hawaii Hotel or similar</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(1N) Sorak Pine Resort or similar</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">(1N) Yanji Pine Resort or similar</span></p>\r\n<p>(2N) Co-op Omogiok Residence or similar</p>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', '<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>', 'Yes', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00', '0000-00-00', 0, '1', NULL, '2021-11-08 16:53:03'),
